-- ECB's Nowotny says never say never on QE, but not now - CNBC
-- By Shadia Nasralla and Angelika Gruber
-- Fri Oct 31, 2014 03:54AM EDT
-- None



VIENNA, Oct 31 (Reuters) - The European but such a programme is not in sight at the moment and the ECB should Central Bank should "never say never" to full-on quantitative easing (QE) not be jolted into action every month, Governing Council member Ewald Nowotny said.

"I think we all have learned in life that we never should say never. But I do not see some perspective at this time for this," Nowotny, who is also the governor of Austria's central bank, said in English when asked in a CNBC interview about "full-on" QE.